\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \relax \fontsize  {9}{10.5}\selectfont  \abovedisplayskip 8.5\p@ plus3\p@ minus4\p@ \belowdisplayskip \abovedisplayskip \abovedisplayshortskip \z@ plus2\p@ \belowdisplayshortskip 4\p@ plus2\p@ minus2\p@ \def \leftmargin \leftmargini \topsep 4\p@ plus2\p@ minus2\p@ \parsep 2\p@ plus\p@ minus\p@ \itemsep \parsep {\leftmargin \leftmargini \topsep 4\p@ plus2\p@ minus2\p@ \parsep 2\p@ plus\p@ minus\p@ \itemsep \parsep }\textit  {Folding of villin headpiece (HP35). (a) Molecular structure, consisting of three $\alpha $-helices (residues $3-10$, $14-19$ and $22-32$) that are connected by two loops. (b) Contact map showing the $42$ native contacts of HP35. (c) Time evolution of the RMSD, compared to $1 - Q$ (with $Q$ being the fraction of native contacts) and $\Phi $ representing the sum over the backbone dihedral angles $\phi _i$ of the three $\alpha $-helices. The right side shows the corresponding free energy curves (in units of $k_B\,T$) along these coordinates.}}}{2}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
