\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{1}{2}{\small \textit {Folding of villin headpiece (HP35). (a) Molecular structure, consisting of three $\alpha $-helices (residues $3-10$, $14-19$ and $22-32$) that are connected by two loops. (b) Contact map showing the $42$ native contacts of HP35. (c) Time evolution of the RMSD, compared to $1 - Q$ (with $Q$ being the fraction of native contacts) and $\Phi $ representing the sum over the backbone dihedral angles $\phi _i$ of the three $\alpha $-helices. The right side shows the corresponding free energy curves (in units of $k_B\,T$) along these coordinates.}}{figure.caption.9}{}}
